09/03/2003
LISBON, Portugal -- Minister of State and Defence Paulo Portas met Friday (7 March) with Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy, pledging his country's active support for Bulgaria's admission to NATO and its active participation as a full member. 
The two officials also discussed bilateral relations and the Iraqi crisis. 
Passy visited Lisbon in advance of a trip there by Bulgarian Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg this week. 
(BTA - 08/03/03)
